==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Trial balance
<hw>Tri"al bal`ance</hw>. <fld>(Bookkeeping)</fld> <def>The testing of a
ledger to discover whether the debits and credits balance, by finding
whether the sum of the personal credits increased by the difference
between the debit and credit sums in the merchandise and other
impersonal accounts equals the sum of personal debits. The equality
would not show that the items were all correctly posted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Triality</ent>⟦br⟧
